<Issue id="43376" key="FAB-17109" number="17109" project="10002" reporter="tock" assignee="tsharris" creator="tock" type="10004" summary="viper config parameter &quot;peer.deliveryclient.reConnectBackoffThreshold&quot; is retrieved incorrectly" priority="4" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2019-11-19 08:21:35.0" updated="2020-03-31 18:20:38.0" resolutiondate="2020-03-31 18:20:38.0" votes="0" watches="3" workflowId="56484"> <description><! CDATA This parameter is specified as duration in the core.yaml file, i.e. "3600s", but is retrieved as if it is a float. (see deliveryclient.go L42) {code:java} func getReConnectBackoffThreshold() float64 { 	return util.GetFloat64OrDefault("peer.deliveryclient.reConnectBackoffThreshold", defaultReConnectBackoffThreshold) } {code} As a result, the default is always in effect in the deliveryservice.broadcastClient , no matter what is in the core.yaml file.  The solution is simple: change getReConnectBackoffThreshold() to first get the value as a time.Duration, and then convert it to a float.  ></description> </Issue>
